docs/npm-publish.md:81:After the pull request lands on `main`, GitHub Actions opens or updates a release pull request. Merging that release pull request runs `pnpm release`, which builds the package and publishes unpublished package versions through Changesets. If npm publish succeeds, the workflow then calls the reusable MoonBit publish workflow so `PerfectPan/agent-finder` is published to mooncakes.io from the same release flow.
